messages.message:
i ran into the exact problem before as well! see thread (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05L87V014J/p1742238526856759?thread_ts=1742174358.255569&cid=C05L87V014J)

this should be sufficient
```pyenv global 3.9.17
cd webserver/api-server

poetry shell
poetry install

# Retry
make build-protos```
(you should be able to skip the `poetry env rm --all` / `rm -rf` part if  your api-server dependencies aren't messed up)

(i messed mine up earlier in the thread :lolcry: )
